M. Mitchell, S. Wu, A. Zaldivar, P. Barnes, L. Vasserman, B. Hutchinson, E. Spitzer, I. D. Raji, and T. Ge-","ANSWER: The attention mechanism addresses several learning challenges in Neural Machine Translation by enabling models to focus on relevant parts of input sequences during the generation process. This is achieved through soft alignments that compute weights for each position in both source and target sequences based on their contribution to the output at every time step. By allowing these weighted sums across positions, the attention mechanism allows the model to dynamically select the most important words from the input sequence when generating an output word, thereby improving translation quality and reducing vanishing gradient problems. However, the specific implementation details, methodologies, and mathematical concepts used for implementing the attention mechanism are not explicitly mentioned within the given context.","The attention mechanism addresses several learning challenges in Neural Machine Translation by enabling models to focus on relevant parts of input sequences during the generation process. This is achieved through soft alignments that compute weights for each position in both source and target sequences based on their contribution to the output at every time step. By allowing these weighted sums across positions, the attention mechanism allows the model to dynamically select the most important words from the input sequence when generating an output word, thereby improving translation quality and reducing vanishing gradient problems. However, the specific implementation details, methodologies, and mathematical concepts used for implementing the attention mechanism are not explicitly mentioned within the given context."
