We considered ﬁltering the dataset to remove toxic content","In the given context, there is no direct mention of the Rotary Position Embedding (RoPE) approach in Transformers. However, I can explain how RoPE differs from the traditional additive method of position embedding based on general knowledge about these techniques.

The traditional additive method embeds positional information into self-attention layers of transformer models through learnable vectors added to each token representation before processing. This addition helps the model understand the relative positions between tokens during the self-attention process.

On the other hand, Rotary Position Embeddings (RoPE) propose a different way to incorporate positional information. Instead of adding fixed or learned positional embeddings, RoPE multiplies the sinusoidal functions of the dimensions of the input embeddings with specific frequencies. These frequencies are designed such that they encode both absolute and relative position information within the sequence. By doing so, RoPE eliminates the need for predefined positional embeddings while maintaining the positional awareness in transformers.","In the given context, there is no direct mention of the Rotary Position Embedding (RoPE) approach in Transformers. However, I can explain how RoPE differs from the traditional additive method of position embedding based on general knowledge about these techniques. The traditional additive method embeds positional information into self-attention layers of transformer models through learnable vectors added to each token representation before processing. This addition helps the model understand the relative positions between tokens during the self-attention process. On the other hand, Rotary Position Embeddings (RoPE) propose a different way to incorporate positional information. Instead of adding fixed or learned positional embeddings, RoPE multiplies the sinusoidal functions of the dimensions of the input embeddings with specific frequencies. These frequencies are designed such that they encode both absolute and relative position information within the sequence. By doing so, RoPE eliminates the need for predefined positional embeddings while maintaining the positional awareness in transformers."
