The use of tools and external resources can significantly enhance the capabilities of large language models in practical applications as demonstrated by various research works. For instance, Pranav et al. developed Squad, which utilizes SFT+PPO (offline), presumably a reinforcement learning method that allows the model to learn from data without real-world interaction. On the other hand, Ofir et al. employed GPT-3 and neural re-ranking techniques to measure QA performance more effectively at the European Conference on Information Retrieval. Lastly, Jayr et al. introduced Visconde, a multi-document system that might utilize external resources like knowledge bases or APIs to improve its understanding and reasoning abilities. These examples illustrate how different approaches leverage tools and external resources to extend the functionalities of large language models.","The use of tools and external resources can significantly enhance the capabilities of large language models in practical applications as demonstrated by various research works. For instance, Pranav et al. developed Squad, which utilizes SFT+PPO (offline), presumably a reinforcement learning method that allows the model to learn from data without real-world interaction. On the other hand, Ofir et al. employed GPT-3 and neural re-ranking techniques to measure QA performance more effectively at the European Conference on Information Retrieval. Lastly, Jayr et al. introduced Visconde, a multi-document system that might utilize external resources like knowledge bases or APIs to improve its understanding and reasoning abilities. These examples illustrate how different approaches leverage tools and external resources to extend the functionalities of large language models."
