CONTEXT: latency and smaller throughput due to reduced cache availability. To alleviate this issue, we use sliding window attention...

ANSWER: In terms of the relationship between question answering model performance and the size of the model, it is not explicitly mentioned within the given context how the performance varies with the size of the model. However, the usage of sliding window attention mechanism might suggest an indirect impact on scale. Sliding window attention allows each token to attend to a limited number of tokens from the previous layer (W=3, as stated), which potentially imposes some constraints on the model capacity compared to full self-attention mechanisms used in transformer architectures. As more layers are added, the range over which information propagates increases exponentially (k×W tokens), suggesting potential limitations on long-range dependencies handling as the model grows larger. Nonetheless, without further specifics about the exact nature of our model architecture, it remains difficult to draw definitive conclusions regarding the influence of model size on performance.","CONTEXT: latency and smaller throughput due to reduced cache availability. To alleviate this issue, we use sliding window attention... ANSWER: In terms of the relationship between question answering model performance and the size of the model, it is not explicitly mentioned within the given context how the performance varies with the size of the model. However, the usage of sliding window attention mechanism might suggest an indirect impact on scale. Sliding window attention allows each token to attend to a limited number of tokens from the previous layer (W=3, as stated), which potentially imposes some constraints on the model capacity compared to full self-attention mechanisms used in transformer architectures. As more layers are added, the range over which information propagates increases exponentially (k×W tokens), suggesting potential limitations on long-range dependencies handling as the model grows larger. Nonetheless, without further specifics about the exact nature of our model architect